{"session_id": 47, "bill_id": 13428, "bill_type": "Senate Bill", "bill_number": 31, "bill_title": "to provide rule-making authority to the Department of Environment and Natural Resources to carry out the requirements of the federal Safe Drinking Water Act amendments of 1996.", "sponsors": [], "keywords": ["Administrative Rules", "Environmental Protection"], "audio": [], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 13428, "bill_version_id": 78015, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "1998-01-07T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to provide rule-making authority to the Department of Environment and Natural Resources to carry out the requirements of the federal Safe Drinking Water Act amendments of 1996. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 34A-3A be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: In order to carry out the requirements of the federal Safe Drinking Water Act as amended to August 6, 1996, the secretary of environment and natural resources shall promulgate rules, pursuant to chapter 1-26, establishing: (1) Procedures for a supplier of water to demonstrate that a new system intended to be a public water system has the technical, managerial, and financial capacity to achieve and maintain compliance with all relevant local, state, and federal requirements; (2) Procedures for the department to issue certificates of approval to new water suppliers once a technical, managerial, and financial capacity review, consistent with provisions of this chapter, is completed. The rules shall provide that a new system intended to be a public water system, after October 1, 1999, may not operate until it has been issued a certificate of approval; (3) The development and implementation of a strategy to assist public water systems in acquiring and maintaining technical, managerial, and financial capacity to comply with all relevant local, state, and federal requirements; and (4) Such other rules as may be necessary to implement the provisions of the federal Safe Drinking Water Act as amended to August 6, 1996, in a state drinking water program approved by the United States Environmental Protection Agency. A violation of any rule adopted pursuant to this section is subject to the penalties provided for in \u00a7 34A-3A-3."}, {"bill_id": 13428, "bill_version_id": 78014, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "1998-02-18T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 13428, "action_date": "1998-01-13T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 76884, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/76884.pdf", "status_text": "First read in Senate and referred to", "journal_page": 25, "committee_id_action": 601, "committee_id_assigned": 574, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 13428, "action_date": "1998-01-20T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 76526, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/76526.pdf", "status_text": "Do Pass,", "journal_page": 112, "committee_id_action": 574, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "P", "vote": {"vote_id": 39145, "president_vote": null, "Yea": [2102, 2103, 2138, 2140, 2175, 2191, 2121], "Excused": [2149], "Nay": [2094]}}, {"bill_id": 13428, "action_date": "1998-01-21T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 76896, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/76896.pdf", "status_text": "Do Pass,", "journal_page": 155, "committee_id_action": 601, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "P", "vote": {"vote_id": 39642, "president_vote": null, "Yea": [2094, 2095, 2102, 2103, 2112, 2115, 2118, 2121, 2122, 2129, 2130, 2135, 2137, 2138, 2140, 2142, 2145, 2148, 2149, 2155, 2156, 2165, 2166, 2169, 2170, 2175, 2179, 2182, 2187, 2188, 2191, 2196], "Excused": [2099, 2125, 2189]}}, {"bill_id": 13428, "action_date": "1998-01-22T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 76897, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/76897.pdf"